Create Emp Table with the following attributes
EmpNo Primary key
Ename Not Null
Job
DOB
Salary
Gender
Write the queries for the following
1. Calculate the square root of the salary of all employees.
2. Format the salary attribute
3. Apply any other five numeric built in function to ‘salary’ attribute of employee table
4. Extract only the first 5 characters of the employee names.
5. Extract second letter and third letter of the employee names.
6. Apply any other five string built in function to ‘name’ attribute of employee table
7. Determine the max and min salary and rename the column as max_salary and
min_salary.
8. Display the month name of date “14-Apr-23” in full.
9. Display the DOB of all employees in the format “dd-mm-yy”.
10. Display the date two months after the DOB of employees.
11. Display the last date of the month in “05-Oct-22”.
12. Display the rounded date in the year format, month format, day format
13. Display the date 60 days before current date.
14. Display the date 14 days after current date.
15. Display the names and DOB of all employees who were born in August.
16. List out the employee names who will celebrate their birthdays during current
month.
17. List all female employees who were born April
18. Fill all null values of salary attribute to 10000
